<paragraph blockId="2.[811,1421,361,1649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis box="[813,1386,501,525]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,978,501,525]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Identification.</emphasis>
This species is easily identified as
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiahyna">
<emphasis box="[1398,1421,502,525]" inLineHeading="true" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">F.</emphasis>
apiahyna
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[919,950,535,559]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the following characters: basidiome perennial, ungulate (
<figureCitation box="[1016,1101,569,593]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[168,231,1954,1974]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia apiahynat. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F.impercepta." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) with hymenophoral surface and pores circular to angular, 5–7 per mm (
<figureCitation box="[1271,1354,602,627]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[168,231,1954,1974]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia apiahynat. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F.impercepta." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); context woody, yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1238,636,660]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="3.[168,231,1954,1974]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,160,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[168,1419,160,1933]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figure 2. Macroscopic structures (hymenophore, pileal region, pores of hymenophore, tubes and context). A. Fomitiporia apiahynat. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F.impercepta." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); hyphal system dimitic, with generative hyphae hyaline, thin-walled, septate (
<figureCitation box="[906,993,704,728]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); skeletal hyphae abundant, yellowish, thick-walled, nonseptate (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1174,737,761]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); basidiospores dextrinoid, subglobose, hyaline, thick-walled, 6–7.5 × 5.8–6 μm (
<figureCitation box="[863,947,805,829]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[169,232,1980,2000]" captionTargetBox="[171,1412,187,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-13@6.[169,1419,184,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 4. Microscopic structures (generative hyphae - left; skeletal hyphae - right; basidiospores). A. Fomitiporia apiahyna. B. F. calkinsii. C. F. conyana. D. F. impercepta. E. F. langloisii. F.F. maxonii. G. F.murrillii. H. F.neotropica." pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="325" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[811,1421,361,1649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,931,844,868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Remarks..</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[942,1185,844,868]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiahyna">
<emphasis box="[942,1185,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fomitiporia apiahyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a worldwide species
</emphasis>
, but curiously there are few records in Neotropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Ryvarden, L" box="[820,998,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" refId="ref6163" refString="Ryvarden, L (2004) Neotropical Polypores, part 1: introduction, Hymenochaetaceae and Ganodermataceae. Synopsis fungorum, volume 9. Fungiflora, Oslo, Norway, 227 pp." type="book" year="2004">Ryvarden 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Alves-Silva G &amp; Reck MA &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Bittencourt F &amp; Robledo GL &amp; Goes-Neto A &amp; Drechsler-Santos ER" box="[1021,1313,911,935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="769 - 790" refId="ref4835" refString="Alves-Silva G, Reck MA, Silveira RMB, Bittencourt F, Robledo GL, Goes-Neto A, Drechsler-Santos ER (2020 b) The Neotropical Fomitiporia (Hymenochaetales, Basidiomycota): the redefinition of F. apiahyna s. s. allows revealing a high hidden species diversity. Mycological Progress 19: 769 - 790. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01593 - 5" type="journal article" year="2020">Alves-Silva et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
corroborated this hypothesis and found that the geographical distributions of species in this complex are extremely important in their classification. 
<taxonomicName box="[1180,1420,1012,1036]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiahyna">
<emphasis box="[1180,1420,1012,1036]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Fomitiporia apiahyna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[821,958,1047,1070]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">sensu stricto</emphasis>
) is not part of the clade of species in the Amazon region; it is restricted to Araucária Moist Forest ecoregion. Our specimens have a basidiospores that are larger on average (6–7.5 × 5.8–6 μm) than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alves-Silva &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[1300,1419,1148,1171]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="conyana">
<emphasis box="[1300,1419,1148,1171]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. conyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–5.5 × 4–5 μm), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alves-Silva, R. M. Silveira &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[1023,1144,1181,1205]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="murrillii">
<emphasis box="[1023,1144,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. murrillii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–6 × 5–6), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alves-Silva, Bittencourt &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nubicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. nubicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(5–6 × 5–6). Thus, we classify our specimens as 
<emphasis box="[814,967,1248,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName box="[814,930,1249,1272]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiayna">F. apiayna</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[938,967,1248,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as 
<emphasis box="[1011,1169,1249,1272]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName box="[1011,1127,1249,1272]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="apiayna">F. apiayna</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1134,1169,1249,1272]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="stricto">s.s.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is not part of the clade containing Amazonian species. Our specimens may rep- resent a distinct lineage and potentially a new species in the complex, but phylogenetic studies are needed to prove this hypothesis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="325" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[811,1421,361,1649]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis box="[813,1419,1422,1446]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,961,1422,1446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Distribution.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[974,1261,1422,1446]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<taxonomicName box="[974,1217,1422,1446]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="apiahyna">Fomitiporia apiahyna</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1230,1261,1422,1446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was reported
</emphasis>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[992,1061,1456,1480]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1082,1194,1456,1480]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1214,1306,1456,1480]" name="Ecuador" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1416,1457,1480]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[813,939,1490,1514]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[953,1037,1490,1514]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and Florida (
<bibRefCitation author="Amalfi M &amp; Decock C" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="873 - 887" refId="ref4911" refString="Amalfi M, Decock C (2013) Fomitiporia castilloi sp. nov. and multiple clades around F. apiahyna and F. texana in Meso- and South America evidenced by multiloci phylogenetic inferences. Mycologia 105 (4): 873 - 887. https: // doi. org / 10.3852 / 11 - 423" type="journal article" year="2013">Amalfi and Decock 2013</bibRefCitation>
). According 
<bibRefCitation author="Amalfi M &amp; Decock C" box="[1004,1288,1524,1548]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="873 - 887" refId="ref4911" refString="Amalfi M, Decock C (2013) Fomitiporia castilloi sp. nov. and multiple clades around F. apiahyna and F. texana in Meso- and South America evidenced by multiloci phylogenetic inferences. Mycologia 105 (4): 873 - 887. https: // doi. org / 10.3852 / 11 - 423" type="journal article" year="2013">Amalfi and Decock (2013)</bibRefCitation>
there is one record in the Amazon region, in French Guiana. However 
<bibRefCitation author="Alves-Silva G &amp; Reck MA &amp; Silveira RMB &amp; Bittencourt F &amp; Robledo GL &amp; Goes-Neto A &amp; Drechsler-Santos ER" box="[864,1134,1591,1615]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" pagination="769 - 790" refId="ref4835" refString="Alves-Silva G, Reck MA, Silveira RMB, Bittencourt F, Robledo GL, Goes-Neto A, Drechsler-Santos ER (2020 b) The Neotropical Fomitiporia (Hymenochaetales, Basidiomycota): the redefinition of F. apiahyna s. s. allows revealing a high hidden species diversity. Mycological Progress 19: 769 - 790. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11557 - 020 - 01593 - 5" type="journal article" year="2020">Alves-Silva et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
had shown that this record was actually 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alves-Silva &amp; Drechsler-Santos" authorityYear="2020" box="[954,1074,1626,1649]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Hymenochaetaceae" genus="Fomitiporia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hymenochaetales" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="conyana">
<emphasis box="[954,1074,1626,1649]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">F. conyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
